question_text:
Please write a C function concat(str1, str2, out) that concatenates two given strings, str1 and str2, and store the result into the new variable out. For example,
concat("foo", "bar", out); 
will replace the variable out with "foobar". Please DO NOT use any string manipulation functions in C Standard Library.

answer:
```c
void concat(char *str1, char *str2, char *out) {
  int i = 0, j = 0;
  while (str1[i] != '\0') {
    out[i] = str1[i];
    i++;
  }
  while (str2[j] != '\0') {
    out[i] = str2[j];
    i++;
    j++;
  }
  out[i] = '\0';
}
```

